  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I learn spoken English?",
  "response": "Learning spoken English involves a combination of practicing speaking, listening, and understanding grammar and vocabulary. Here are some comprehensive steps you can follow to improve your spoken English:\n\n1. **Exposure to English**:\n   - **Listen to native speakers**: Watch English movies, TV shows, YouTube videos, and listen to English podcasts. This helps you get familiar with pronunciations, accents, and common expressions.\n   - **Music**: Listen to English songs and try to understand the lyrics.\n\n2. **Speaking Practice**:\n   - **Language Exchange**: Find language partners or language exchange platforms where you can practice speaking with native or fluent English speakers.\n   - **Online Tutors**: Consider platforms like iTalki, Preply, or Cambly where you can hire tutors for one-on-one speaking practice.\n   - **Practice with Friends**: Speak English with friends or family members who are also learning or know the language well.\n\n3. **Study Grammar and Vocabulary**:\n   - **Books and Apps**: Use grammar and vocabulary books, or apps like Duolingo, Babbel, or Memrise to strengthen your understanding.\n   - **Daily Word Challenge**: Learn a new word every day and try to use it in sentences.\n\n4. **Reading Practice**:\n   - **Read Aloud**: Practice reading newspapers, books, or articles out loud. This helps improve pronunciation and fluency.\n   - **Audiobooks**: Follow along with the text while listening to audiobooks.\n\n5. **Writing**:\n   - **Journals**: Maintain an English diary or journal where you write about your day. It helps organize thoughts in English.\n   - **Online Forums**: Participate in online forums or social media discussions to practice writing and think in English.\n\n6. **Understand Cultural Context**:\n   - **Idioms and Slang**: Learn common idioms and slang to understand casual conversational English better.\n\n7. **Pronunciation and Accent Training**:\n   - **Pronunciation Tools**: Use tools like Forvo for pronunciation guides or websites that focus on accent training.\n   - **Imitate Native Speakers**: Try to imitate the accent and intonation of native speakers you listen to.\n\n8. **Regular Practice**:\n   - **Consistency**: Make a schedule and practice regularly to ensure steady progress.\n   - **Record Yourself**: Recording your own speech can help identify areas for improvement.\n\nRemember, practice and patience are key. You\u2019ll improve over time with consistent effort.",
